Taiwan steel shares up on steel rod price hikes . Taiwan ' s steel shares rose at mid - morning on Tuesday on price hikes of domestic steel rods , brokers said . After 90 minutes , Kuei Hung Industry was up 80 cents or 3 . 58 percent to T $ 23 . 20 , and Feng Hsin Iron had gained 60 cents or 1 . 88 percent to T $ 32 . 50 . " These steel rod makers should benefit from the price hikes , but it should be only a short - lived gain , " said Henry Chen , an analyst at Yuan Ta Securities . Chen said that because the property market is widely expected to recover soon , steel makers should anticipate a rise in construction projects . - - Taipei Newsroom ( 5080815 ) 
